data.title: Hyundai Motor Group partners with NVIDIA to develop AI industry in Korea through new AI application and technology centers.
data.description: Hyundai Motor Group and NVIDIA have partnered with the South Korean government to advance South Korea's physical artificial intelligence industry. This collaboration will include creating an AI application center and AI technology center. The aim is to foster local AI talent and cultivate a thriving innovation ecosystem within Hyundai Motor Group.

data.description: LHV Group has disclosed that from October 24th to October 30th, 2025, they purchased their own shares on the Nasdaq Tallinn Stock Exchange.

data.title: Inbank extends Piret Paulus and Erik Kaju's Management Board mandates for 3 years, effective from 31 Oct 2025.
data.description: The Supervisory Board of AS Inbank announced on October 31, 2025, their decision to prolong the tenures of Piret Paulus and Erik Kaju as Members of the Management Board of Inbank AS for another three years.

data.title: Altrio's deal execution platform gains traction with dozens of CRE brokerages in 2025.
data.description: In Toronto on October 28, 2025, Altrio, a prominent technology provider for real estate capital markets, revealed that its comprehensive deal execution platform has seen swift uptake by numerous capital markets teams in the commercial real estate sector. The platform has been embraced by dozens of teams operating in major markets, demonstrating its growing popularity.

data.title: NAR report: Pending home sales unchanged in September, down 0.9% YoY. Shows data on home sales under contract.
data.description: In September, pending home sales in the United States remained stable compared to the previous month, as reported by the National Association of REALTORS® Pending Home Sales Report on Oct. 29, 2025. However, there was a 0.9% decrease in pending home sales year over year. This report serves as a valuable tool for various participants in the real estate market, such as agents, homebuyers, and sellers, by offering insights into the volume of home sales that are under contract.

data.title: NACS Foundation, in collaboration with FoodRecovery.org, recovered 120,000 pounds of surplus food in Chicago, providing 100,292 meals for those facing food insecurity.
data.description: In Alexandria, Virginia, the NACS Foundation collaborated with FoodRecovery.org after the 2025 NACS Show in Chicago to conduct a significant food recovery initiative. They gathered over 120,000 pounds of extra food, drinks, and supplies from 49 exhibitors. This generous contribution resulted in 100,292 meals being provided to those experiencing food insecurity. Additionally, actions were taken given the impending expiration of SNAP benefits for millions of Americans in November.

data.title: Bybit's report on October 2025 rate cut shows mixed markets, uncertainty on December decision. World's 2nd largest crypto exchange.
data.description: In Dubai, UAE on October 31, 2025, Bybit, the cryptocurrency exchange with the second-highest trading volume globally, unveiled its most recent Bybit Crypto Insights Report. The report delves into the market trends after the highly awaited rate cut in October 2025, amidst enduring uncertainty surrounding various factors.

data.title: LRS CEO Matt Spencer honored as one of the "Best and Brightest CEOs in the Nation" by NABR. Celebrating excellence.
data.description: In Rosemont, Illinois on October 31, 2025, LRS revealed that their CEO, Matt Spencer, has been honored as one of the top CEOs in the country by the National Association for Business Resources (NABR). Spencer's recognition as one of the "Best and Brightest CEOs in the Nation" is a significant achievement for LRS and highlights his exceptional leadership skills.

data.title: Georgia travel nurse wins $60K in Medical Solutions national giveaway. Amber Ellis from Leesburg won the prize.
data.description: Savannah, Georgia - In an announcement on October 31, 2025, Medical Solutions, a prominent healthcare workforce partner in the U.S., revealed the selection of Amber Ellis, a travel nurse hailing from Leesburg, Georgia, as the recipient of the grand prize in their Weeks of Impact giveaway. This news showcases the company's commitment to recognizing talent within its workforce, with Amber standing out among participants. The giveaway is a part of the company's initiatives to support and appreciate its employees, consolidating its position as a leader in the healthcare industry.

data.title: TWOPAGES celebrates 10th anniversary in LA with "TWOPAGES TOGETHER" event, marking the end of Design Contest.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, the city of Los Angeles hosted the final events of the TWOPAGES TOGETHER × Design Contest. This celebration commemorated the 10th anniversary of TWOPAGES, a leading provider of contemporary window treatment solutions. The event in Los Angeles was a significant milestone in the company's history, showcasing their commitment to innovative design and dedication to their customers.

data.title: Inventor from Tower City, Pa  develops "EASY RAIL" with increased space and reduced damage; aiming for a revolutionary advancement in handrails or banisters.
data.description: In Pittsburgh on October 31, 2025, an inventor from Tower City, Pennsylvania, shared about their innovative creation, the EASY RAIL. The inventor aimed to revolutionize handrails and banisters with this invention. The EASY RAIL is designed to enhance space and minimize damage while moving bulky furniture or appliances. This invention holds promise for improving safety and efficiency in homes and other spaces.

data.title: Data Center UPS market to reach $12.47 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.3%. Market size was $8.76 billion in 2025.
data.description: In Delray Beach, Florida, on October 31, 2025, it was reported that the Data Center UPS Market is experiencing significant growth, with its market size projected to increase from USD 8.76 billion in 2025 to USD 12.47 billion by 2030. This expansion is expected to result in a Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of 7.3%. Interested individuals can explore 250 market data points related to this trend.

data.title: Pet perfume market expected to grow to $2.7 billion globally by 2034 at 6.7% CAGR due to humanization trends and urban pet ownership.
data.description: The market for pet fragrances is expected to grow significantly, driven by the increasing trend of treating pets as family members, the desire for high-quality grooming items, and the trend towards personalized pet health. The rising number of pets in urban areas and a higher expenditure on pet cleanliness are also boosting this growth.
